The Bauchi Police Command has confirmed the release of former Secretary-General of the defunct Nigeria Football Association (NFA) now Nigeria Football Federation (NFF), Sani Ahmed Toro, who was abducted by gunmen last Tuesday in Nassarawa State. Toro was released with his two other friends Sani Ahmed Toro and Garba Yila. Bauchi police spokesman SP Ahmed Wakil, said they were released around 5 am on Tuesday and are in good health.   We’ll fix Justices’ complaints on work…     Remaining kidnapped railway passengers must be rescued…     Portable needs rehabilitation, says Okowa’s aide   But he did not disclose whether ransom was paid to secure their release or not. The Nation reports the trio was kidnapped at a village around Akwanga in Nasarawa State. They left Abuja around 5.00 pm on Saturday after attending the wedding of the son of a former NFF President, Aminu Maigari and were kidnapped at about 7.30 pm. The kidnappers were said to have demanded N150m ransom.